1. Executive Leadership
Chief Executive Officer (CEO) – Adam Kershner (adam@kahana.co)

Overall responsibility for Kahana’s strategy, including security and compliance.

Approves major security policies and the SOC 2 program.

Chief Technology Officer (CTO)

Owns technology strategy and architecture for Kahana Oasis.

Oversees Engineering and DevOps functions.

Co‑approves key security and technical policies.

Chief Information Security Officer (CISO) / Security Lead

Owns the information security program and SOC 2 control design.

Leads risk assessments, incident response, and security governance.

Coordinates with Engineering, DevOps, HR, and Legal.

Chief Operating Officer (COO) / Operations Lead

Oversees business operations, including business continuity and office/physical security.

Chief Financial Officer (CFO)

Oversees financial reporting and contracts; signs the management assertion letter with the CEO.

(If some C‑level roles are combined, you can note that: e.g., “CTO also acting as Security Lead.”)

2. Product & Engineering
VP / Head of Engineering

Manages software development teams for Oasis.

Responsible for SDLC, code quality, and implementing security requirements in product design.

Engineering Team Leads

Lead feature teams (e.g., “Browser & Client,” “Backend Services,” “AI & Integrations”).

Ensure secure coding, code review, and adherence to Change Management Policy.

Software Engineers

Design, build, and maintain application features.

Follow SDLC, Access Control, and Security policies.

3. DevOps / Infrastructure
DevOps / Infrastructure Lead

Owns cloud infrastructure (AWS, etc.), CI/CD, backup/DR, and monitoring.

Responsible for implementing technical security controls (networking, encryption at rest, logging).

DevOps / SRE Engineers

Manage deployments, infrastructure as code, observability.

Ensure systems meet availability and recovery objectives.

4. Security & Compliance
Security Lead / CISO (as above)

Defines and maintains security policies (access control, logging, vulnerability management, incident response).

Coordinates SOC 2 readiness, evidence collection, and internal audits.

Security / Compliance Analyst (if applicable)

Helps map controls to SOC 2 criteria, gather evidence, and perform internal control testing.

(If you do not yet have a dedicated role, you can list “Security responsibilities currently performed by <Name/Title>.”)

5. Customer Success & Support
Head of Customer Success / Support Lead

Owns customer communication during incidents and continuity events.

Ensures support staff follow data handling and access policies.

Support / Success Team

Handles customer issues through ticketing systems.

Access to customer data limited to what is necessary for support.

6. HR & People Operations
HR / People Lead

Owns hiring, onboarding, offboarding, and background checks.

Ensures employees complete security training and sign policies/NDAs.

HR / People Ops Team

Maintains employee records and onboarding/offboarding checklists.

7. Legal & Privacy
Legal Counsel / Compliance Counsel

Reviews contracts, DPAs, and privacy obligations.

Advises on data retention, incident notification, and regulatory requirements.

8. Operations & Physical Security
Operations / Office Manager

Manages physical office logistics (e.g., Chandigarh office), including visitor logs and access.

Implements physical security controls per the Physical Security Policy.